The paper proposes a method for clustering and topic modeling of document data sets, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The method is based on nonnegative matrix factorization (NMF), which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). The paper also compares its method to other clustering algorithms, which falls under the database (cs.DB) sub-category.
